HEADWORD: Pelopium
<hw>Pe*lo"pi*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>Pelops</ets>, brother of Niobe, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A supposed new metal found in columbite, afterwards shown to be
identical with columbium, or niobium.</def>⟦br⟧
